title: USGS Great Basin Geothermal Data
name: USGS Great Basin Geothermal Data
description:
This data was acquired by USGS and INEEL from CalEnergy, Geothermal Resources International (GEO), Aminoil USA, AMAX and other companies in 1995. Temperature data primarily collected Chevron Geothermal and Phillips Petroleum Company beginning in the 1970s. 

According to USGS, data were obtained using calibrated thermister probes with an accuracy of about 0.1 Â°C. The data were in a variety of formats and units. Most locations were listed as Section, Township, and Range. The data were mostly copies of field data sheets. Some data were found in interpretive reports. Others were analogue temperature-depth plots at various scales. Gradient values shown in the database were obtained from the field data sheets or plots. These were usually based on a visual straight-line fit of the data from the lowermost section of the hole. The original data (available at the link below) indicated where data were not available, where the temperature gradient was isothermal, or when the gradient was non-conductive. These three conditions are all represented by '0' in the data here.

Source: http://pubs.usgs.gov/of/1999/of99-425/webmaps/home.html
